Process:\
After going through multiple datasets, I had finally settled the Hitchiti Experimental Forest data set. I first began to break down the data into smaller categories, selecting specific or groups of variables to get smaller data sets. Secondly, I explored the metadata files to obtain the species master list, which I used to relate the Species column in the data set, originally a number, to their common name. I stored this data in a new column, dubbed speciesName. Beyond that, I read the rest of the metadata to get a better understanding of the process and the study that was done, as well as to better understanding the meaning and significance behind each column.\
\
Design Decisions:\
I wanted to convey basic information in an exploratory way, as well as display trends within the data. To do this, I chose a histogram and a pie chart because they are user friendly and very readable. They both give information at a glance, and are good for understanding data as a whole. I chose a scatterplot in order to display trends and allow the user to manipulate data.\
